Test description

Authentication

API key

An API key is a special token (Authorization) that you need to provide in header when making API calls, Like: { Authorization: "TOKEN_VALUE" }

    method: 'POST', 
    body: {

api_token_create

token pair to prove the authentication of those credentials.

  • Response

    "password": ""

  • password String

                                                                        • Request
                                                                        • Response
                                                                        • Coding

                                                                        formData

                                                                        publisherUserId REQUIRED

                                                                        email OPTIONAL

                                                                        string

                                                                        firstName OPTIONAL

                                                                        string

                                                                        lastName OPTIONAL

                                                                        • password String
                                                                        • profilePicture String
                                                                        cURL JavaScript Node Python 
                                                                        curl --request POST \
  --url https://devpub.gamergraph.io//publisheruser/update/ \
  --header 'Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded' \
  --form 'publisherUserId=0' \
  --form 'email=Something' \
  --form 'firstName=Something' \
  --form 'lastName=Something' \
  --form 'password=Something' \
  --form 'profilePicture=@FILE'

    method: 'POST', 
    headers: {
        "Content-Type": "application/x-www-form-urlencoded"
    }, 
    body: 'publisherUserId=0&email=Something&firstName=Something&lastName=Something&password=Something&profilePicture=@FILE', 
}) 
.then(e => e.json()) 
.then((data) => { 
    console.log('Request succeeded with JSON response', data); 
}) 
.catch((error) => { 
    console.log('Request failed', error); 
});

    url: 'https://devpub.gamergraph.io//role/list/', 
};

    if (error) throw new Error(error);
 
    console.log(body); 
});
